Source: unifont
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian QA Group <packages@qa.debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.6.2
Build-Depends-Indep: xfonts-utils
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.31)

Package: unifont
Architecture: all
Recommends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: X11 dual-width GNU Unicode font
 The GNU Unicode font is an X11 bitmap font in iso10646 encoding. It is
 useful if you have X programs such as the yudit text editor that are
 Unicode aware.

Package: unifont-bin
Architecture: all
Description: Miscellaneous utilities associated with unifont
 This package provides other utilities that are part of the unifont source
 package but are not necessary for using the font itself:
 .
  - unifont.hex: Unprocessed font in "hex" format
  - hexdraw: Produces human-readable representation of .hex fonts
